President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday condoled with the family, All Progressives Congress (APC), the government and people of Kaduna State over the death of Alhaji Umar Gana after protracted illness.
The President in a statement by Garba Shehu,Â Senior Special Assistant to the President, Media and Publicity, acknowledged that Alhaji Gana made enormous contributions towards the successes recorded by the APC at the 2015 and 2019 presidential and governorship elections, during which he served as Coordinator and member of the Campaign Council, respectively.
President Buhari prayed that God will comfort the family of the dedicated departed politician and grant rest to his soul.